# Comments

Only add comments that explain **why**, not **what**. The code should speak for itself.

## Do not write

- Comments that restate the next line (`// Check if nil`, `// Return the result`, `// Get the branch`)
- Comments that narrate control flow (`// Loop through items`, `// Handle error`)
- Comments that label obvious variable assignments (`// Create the map`)

## Do write

- Doc comments on exported types and functions (required by Go convention)
- Non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints the code can't convey
- Section labels in complex multi-branch logic (e.g. XML/YAML manipulation with 3+ branches)
- Magic numbers or offsets that need explanation

## Test files

Test comments describing setup steps or scenario intent within a large test function are acceptable — they help navigate long test bodies.
